rshall s life to illustrate key leadership rubrics  Colonel Husted s book was published in December 2006 by the Army War College and distributed by Stackpole Books  The 264 page book is available in hardback  23 95  in bookstores and on line at Barnes   Noble  Books a Million  and Amazon  All royalties from the book are donated to the Fisher House Foundation to assist families of wounded veterans  Col  Husted  who teaches the Business Leadership   the Classics elective  will be the subject of a feature interview story about George C  Marshall in the May June issue of WWII magazine  Spring 2007 Newsletter  AACSB Accreditation  Field Test BU  Mission Statement  New Faculty Faces  New Book Released  Faculty Research  Speakers  Engineering Initiative  Cadet Research  Cadet Investment Group  Cadet Internships  Class of 2005  Cadet Field Trip  Cadet Awards  Hinman Award  Stay Connected  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 